[5] Fiji
Date: Wed 8 Oct 2008
Source: Radio New Zealand International [edited]
<http://www.rnzi.com/pages/news.php?op=read&id=42398>


Fiji's ministry of health says more than 1800 people are now
suffering from dengue fever. The country declared a dengue outbreak
on 2 Sep [2008].

The ministry's director of primary preventative health services, Dr
Losevati Alefaio, says it's affecting everyone, and the youngest
victim is a 2-month-old baby.

"We had a total of 1849 cases. That's for the whole of Fiji. It still
hasn't moved away from the central division and the western division.
That's where the cases are mostly."

Dr Losevati Alefaio says the ministry is spraying and running public
awareness campaigns but adds the public must get rid of water
containers where larvae breed and wear insect repellent at all times.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of dengue cases on Fiji has nearly doubled since the
report of 25 Sep 2008 (see ProMED archive no. 20080929.3078).

